21#include "mpc-impl.h"
22
23int
24mpc_sinh (mpc_ptr rop, mpc_srcptr op, mpc_rnd_t rnd)
25{
26 /* sinh(op) = -i*sin(i*op) = conj(-i*sin(conj(-i*op))) */
27 mpc_t z;
28 mpc_t sin_z;
29 int inex;
30
31 /* z := conj(-i * op) and rop = conj(-i * sin(z)), in other words, we have
32 to switch real and imaginary parts. Let us set them without copying
33 significands. */
34 mpc_realref (z)[0] = mpc_imagref (op)[0];
35 mpc_imagref (z)[0] = mpc_realref (op)[0];
36 mpc_realref (sin_z)[0] = mpc_imagref (rop)[0];
37 mpc_imagref (sin_z)[0] = mpc_realref (rop)[0];
38
39 inex = mpc_sin (sin_z, z, MPC_RND (MPC_RND_IM (rnd), MPC_RND_RE (rnd)));
40
41 /* sin_z and rop parts share the same significands, copy the rest now. */
42 mpc_realref (rop)[0] = mpc_imagref (sin_z)[0];
43 mpc_imagref (rop)[0] = mpc_realref (sin_z)[0];
44
45 /* swap inexact flags for real and imaginary parts */
46 return MPC_INEX (MPC_INEX_IM (inex), MPC_INEX_RE (inex));
47}
